vectorData.altText: 16. The ________ _______ nerve is associated with abduction of the hip.
That's right!  The superior gluteal nerve innervates gluteus medius, minimus and tensor fascia lata. Gluteus medius and minimus act to abduct and medially rotate the hip!
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Recall that the superior gluteal nerve innervates the gluteus medius and minimus and the tensor fascia lata. What actions is it responsible for? Think then click     !
The inferior gluteal nerve innervates the gluteus maximus. What movements is it responsible for? Think then click     !
Gluteus maximus: extension and lateral rotation of the hip.

Gluteus medius and minimus: abduction and medial rotation of the hip.
TFL: medial rotation and flexion of the hip.
